Sentencas: Nanoporous 1-mu m thin La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta (LSC) layers are deposited by spray pyrolysis and subsequently sintered at 600 degrees C, 800 degrees C, and 1000 degrees C. A strontium- and oxygen-rich phase can be found within the pore network, which appears at low sintering temperatures.
Titulo: Influence of strontium-rich pore-filling phase on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes

Sentencas: This so-called secondary phase occupies up to 20.7 vol.% of the LSC films for the 600 degrees C annealing process.
Titulo: Influence of strontium-rich pore-filling phase on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes

Sentencas: It does not hinder the electrochemical activity towards oxygen reduction of such layers that exhibit an area-specific resistance (ASR) as low as 0.13 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Influence of strontium-rich pore-filling phase on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes

Sentencas: This result makes the spray pyrolysed LSC thin films promising candidates as intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathodes.
Titulo: Influence of strontium-rich pore-filling phase on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes

Sentencas: For higher sintering temperatures the secondary phase progressively disappears.
Titulo: Influence of strontium-rich pore-filling phase on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes

Sentencas: A correlation between the inverse of the ASR and the whole LSC surface area (regardless of the presence of the secondary phase or not) is also evidenced.
Titulo: Influence of strontium-rich pore-filling phase on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes

Sentencas: The increase of ASR with increasing sintering temperature is found to be primarily related to the exchange neutral flux density of the Sr-deficient LSC.
Titulo: Influence of strontium-rich pore-filling phase on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ thin-film cathodes
